node.text:
Full showcase of my Spirit Blossom Lillia cosplay! I made this cosplay in 2020 and filmed this showcase as part of my @ultimatecosplaychampionship submission, for which I was fortunate enough to receive a judge’s choice award for 😊 
The shoot was very challenging due to lack of mobility, but I’m so happy I was able to work with an amazing videographer to really do this cosplay justice!

✨Videographer: @kroma.productions 
✨Character from @leagueoflegends 
✨Centaur cosplay inspired by @itsginnydi’s centaurette cosplay 

{#leagueoflegendscosplay#leaguecosplay#spiritblossomlillia#cosplay}

node.text:
❄️ 𝑲𝒂𝒎𝒊𝒔𝒂𝒕𝒐 𝑨𝒚𝒂𝒌𝒂 ❄️

New costest!🥳 My next big cosplay project will be Ayaka from Genshin Impact, so I thought I’d start out by doing a makeup test for her! Obviously I haven’t made the outfit yet- I’ve only styled the wig and made part of the hairpiece, but I’m liking how she’s looking so far ☺️

I WILL be making a full tutorial book for Ayaka, which I will be posting on Patre0n! This means I’ll be relaunching it either this month or next. I hope you guys are as excited as I am for her!💙✨

{#genshinimpact#genshinimpactcosplay#ayaka#ayakacosplay#inazuma}

node.text:
I MOVED!!!💜💗✨

I’ve spent the past week moving into a new flat! I now have my own  cosplay space, decorated with as much purple as my heart desires 💜 It’s still not a full workshop, but it’s definitely a step in the right direction and I know I’m going to feel inspired working here ☺️

Eventually I’m hoping to start streaming, potentially genshin, crafting or 3D modelling. But for now…ONTO MAKING AYAKA!❄️❄️

{#cosplaygirl#egirl#ukcosplayer#kda}

node.text:
✨💫Cosplay vs character💫✨ 

Doing a side by side comparison like this after completing a cosplay is always so satisfying!😌 Since I only had 5 weeks to make this I had to plan EVERYTHING out from the start and make sure I didn’t miss any details. This was quite a new way for me to work since I usually break everything down in small sections and take a “make it up as I go along” approach 😅 

Although it was stressful making a big cosplay like this in such a short space of time, it’s good to know that I’m capable of it now!😊

{#leagueoflegendscosplay#leagueoflegends#leaguecosplay#lolcosplay#sentineldiana#cosplayvscharacter}

node.text:
3 years of cosplaying Diana 🌙✨

💜2016 - Dark Valkyrie
🐉2020 - Dragonslayer
💫2021 - Sentinel 

Which weapon is your favourite?? Mine will probably always be Dark Valkyrie…even though it’s a complete mess up close since it was my first ever worbla weapon 😅 The earlier cosplays make look more “impressive” but the Sentinel skin that I just finished is definitely constructed a lot better!

{#leagueoflegends#leagueoflegendscosplay#lolcosplay#dianacosplay}

node.text:
💫SENTINEL DIANA💫

She’s here and she’s FINISHED!!!😱 I can’t explain how good it feels to be finished this costume, I’m still shocked I managed to finish it in under 5 weeks!

I was extremely blessed to have the opportunity to work with @leagueoflegends/@ukleagueoflegends on this cosplay as part of the Sentinels of Light event. This has been a dream of mine for years, and getting to work on Diana especially has been amazing since the character means so much to me ☺️

Thank you for all you guys’ incredible support throughout making this, I’ll be doing a big photoshoot this weekend and can’t wait to show you the final images!😍

{#leagueoflegends#leagueoflegendscosplay#leaguecosplay#sentineldiana#sentinelsoflight#dianacosplay#cosplay}
